race.comment: Good race, and excited to see smart mare KNOBELAS (5) resume. She went through the grades impressively as a 3yo, winning by big spaces at her second and third starts, then starting $1.90 in a good race at Flemington when overrun late. She profiles as a mare that could reach group class and if that's the case, she should be going close here despite giving away fitness. MERCURIAL LADY (6) could be an improver going to 1400m. She may have been unsuited staying at 1200m at Caulfield Heath last start but still ran well, now she can be allowed to roll forward and set a good tempo. EXPRESS GUARD (4) has been building nicely this time in and should be right there. KHADIME (8) won dominantly here last time and can measure up.
